Shares prices were mostly higher at theoustset, bouyed by the latest opinion polls, one of which showsthe ruling Conservative party having a 13 point lead over theLabour opposition party. Record closes on both the New york andTokyo stock exchanges supported market sentiment.    Dealers expect the market to open around five to eightpoints higher but then ease back should buying support fail toemerge. The market appears fairly convinced of a Conservativewin in the next general election but is likely to be restrainedby uncertainty over its timing.    Unilever rose 18p to 2,589 and British Telecom 2p to 254. REUTER&#3;